00:59:36.664 --> 00:59:39.131
LAURA: No, Trinket goes ow, ow, and then he comes
back out.

00:59:39.131 --> 00:59:42.283
MATT: He gets back out of the water, and he's
like-- you see like the (sizzling) off of him.

00:59:42.283 --> 00:59:46.033
LAURA: Trinket, I didn't even tell you to do that,
you just did that on your own! And then--

00:59:46.033 --> 00:59:47.568
MATT: If a bear could shrug--

00:59:47.568 --> 00:59:53.559
LAURA: Yeah, you know. And then I'm going to get
on my broom--

00:59:53.559 --> 00:59:55.254
MATT: What is a whale?

00:59:55.254 --> 01:00:07.816
LAURA: What's a whale? I get on my broom and I
want to fly up and over, above Grog.

01:00:07.816 --> 01:00:13.605
MATT: Okay, so you (whoosh) over, and as you get
up, you almost bump into the ceiling

01:00:13.605 --> 01:00:15.036
where that tower is.

01:00:15.036 --> 01:00:19.319
LAURA: Actually, could I actually get to Grog if I
was flying?

01:00:19.376 --> 01:00:24.863
MATT: If you were flying from here? You could get
right over there and see him on the ground, yeah.

01:00:24.863 --> 01:00:27.086
LAURA: I couldn't get down to him, though?

01:00:27.086 --> 01:00:29.055
MATT: You could get right down to him.

01:00:29.055 --> 01:00:39.248
LAURA: Oh, this is going to be the worst move ever
if it doesn't work. I'm going to get down to where

01:00:39.248 --> 01:00:45.154
Grog is. This is so stupid, though! No, because if
it doesn't work I can't get away! Because that's

01:00:45.154 --> 01:00:46.449
all my movement, isn't it?

01:00:46.449 --> 01:00:48.151
TRAVIS: Let's team up, you and me.

01:00:48.151 --> 01:00:49.608
MATT: What are you doing?

01:00:49.608 --> 01:00:58.644
LAURA: You want to team up? I go down to Grog and
I say, let's shake on it.

01:00:58.727 --> 01:01:02.780
But I take my necklace
off and I put it into my hand.

01:01:02.780 --> 01:01:07.364
TALIESIN and MARISHA: Oh!

01:01:07.364 --> 01:01:09.351
MATT: Make a deception check.

01:01:09.351 --> 01:01:11.387
TRAVIS: Which is not hard.

01:01:11.387 --> 01:01:19.497
LAURA: Oh, it's a one. Whatever. I still try to
touch it to him. Whatever, he doesn't do it.

01:01:19.497 --> 01:01:21.574
MATT: Right. So Grog, do you accept it?

01:01:21.574 --> 01:01:24.502
TRAVIS: No.

01:01:24.502 --> 01:01:27.679
MATT: Okay. She still touches it to you, but
you're not willing,

01:01:27.679 --> 01:01:30.078
so what's the saving throw on that?

01:01:30.078 --> 01:01:32.571
LAURA: It's a wisdom saving throw.

01:01:32.571 --> 01:01:34.430
TRAVIS: You sneaky.

01:01:34.430 --> 01:01:37.251
LAURA: It's only a ten.

01:01:37.251 --> 01:01:45.105
TRAVIS: That's okay, it's not a high modifier.
That's a five.

01:01:45.105 --> 01:01:55.868
MATT: (suction sound) Grog, you are absorbed into
a familiar dark stony throne room, staring out

01:01:55.868 --> 01:02:02.031
through this small open space, almost like a
personalized movie theater of

01:02:02.031 --> 01:02:03.735
the outside of the necklace.

01:02:03.735 --> 01:02:05.192
TRAVIS: How do I get out?

01:02:05.192 --> 01:02:07.551
LAURA: You can't unless I release you.

01:02:07.551 --> 01:02:16.669
MATT: She has to release you. Mind you, Vex, the
battle cannot be won until all the other people

01:02:16.669 --> 01:02:18.610
have been defeated. This is not considered
defeat.

01:02:18.610 --> 01:02:20.071
TALIESIN: You could release him into the acid,
though.

01:02:20.071 --> 01:02:22.004
LAURA: Hey, man. My mind's already there.

01:02:22.004 --> 01:02:30.048
MATT: Remember, just be aware, if you're the last
one standing after everything else happens and you

01:02:30.048 --> 01:02:33.334
release Grog, he's going to destroy you, so think
tactically.

01:02:33.384 --> 01:02:42.423
LAURA: Yes, I plan on it, believe me. I'm going to
use my bonus action to stay hidden from... for my

01:02:42.423 --> 01:02:46.576
skirmisher stealth, can I pick a target? I want to
stay hidden from Keyleth.

01:02:46.576 --> 01:02:49.961
MATT: Okay. You cannot, because in order to get
there, your full movement leaves you right in the

01:02:49.961 --> 01:02:54.102
doorway where she can see you. You literally
landed, did that to Grog, and turned over your

01:02:54.102 --> 01:02:56.762
shoulder and see a giant fire elemental looking
right at you.

01:02:56.762 --> 01:02:59.379
LAURA: Great. So I can't use my bonus action to
hide, because she's right there.

01:02:59.379 --> 01:03:01.089
MATT: Yep, because you're not behind anything.

01:03:01.089 --> 01:03:06.872
LAURA: Tight. I'm going to then use my skirmisher
to stay hidden from Percy,

01:03:06.872 --> 01:03:12.698
and I've got nothing I can do.

01:03:12.698 --> 01:03:16.925
TRAVIS: Fuck. Fuck! Like a rat in a cage.

01:03:16.925 --> 01:03:20.553
MATT: You're just (groans).

01:03:20.553 --> 01:03:24.121
TALIESIN: I imagine this as the interior of the
genie bottle from I Dream of Jeannie.

01:03:24.121 --> 01:03:26.587
Pink and plush.

01:03:26.749 --> 01:03:30.753
TRAVIS: Really? I was picturing something from
Saw, like the inside is just awful.

01:03:30.816 --> 01:03:36.126
MATT: The inside is essentially a 20-by-20-foot
cold stone room with a central stone throne, and

01:03:36.126 --> 01:03:40.061
the view you have is this ten-foot-by-five-foot
slit window that looks out from the necklace.

01:03:40.061 --> 01:03:41.338
TRAVIS: Is it fish-eyed?

01:03:41.338 --> 01:03:47.935
MATT: No, it's just a perspective. This is what
Galdrick, the wolf, had been looking through for

01:03:47.935 --> 01:03:56.168
hundreds of years. And what Trinket looks through
whenever he's trapped. That's your turn, Vex.

01:03:56.216 --> 01:03:58.885
Keyleth, you're up. What are you doing?

01:03:58.885 --> 01:04:00.392
MARISHA: Oh shit.

01:04:00.392 --> 01:04:02.912
SAM: It's like prison. You could do some
push-ups.

01:04:02.912 --> 01:04:09.172
TRAVIS: I'm going to Rocky montage this shit.
Wait, are you skipping me?

01:04:09.172 --> 01:04:14.028
MATT: Oh, that's right, you're up next. Grog, what
do you want to do?

01:04:14.028 --> 01:04:21.056
TRAVIS: I'm going to flip the fuck out! I'm inside
of a goddamn box! I'm going to take my Dwarven

01:04:21.056 --> 01:04:25.835
Thrower and throw it as hard as I can at the
window!

01:04:25.835 --> 01:04:28.432
MATT: Okay. Go ahead and roll an attack.

01:04:28.432 --> 01:04:37.108
TRAVIS: Yep. Reckless! Yep. Almost a natural 20.
26.

01:04:37.108 --> 01:04:39.017
MATT: Go ahead and roll damage.

01:04:39.017 --> 01:04:47.980
TRAVIS: Awesome. I'm getting out of here in no
time. 25.

01:04:47.980 --> 01:04:50.540
MATT: All right. Damage?

01:04:50.540 --> 01:04:51.984
TRAVIS: Yeah, 25 damage.

01:04:51.984 --> 01:04:55.478
MATT: Okay. Good. You are also technically sieged
because of your gauntlets.

01:04:55.478 --> 01:04:56.932
TRAVIS: That's right, double damage.

01:04:56.932 --> 01:05:06.212
MATT: All right. As you slam your axe into the
front of this, you watch as the stone (rumble)

01:05:06.212 --> 01:05:10.517
quakes a little bit, and a little bit of dust
(hiss) settles from the ceiling.

01:05:10.517 --> 01:05:12.709
TALIESIN: Oh my god.

01:05:12.709 --> 01:05:13.968
TRAVIS: Oh, really?

01:05:13.968 --> 01:05:16.417
LAURA: He could bust out of the necklace.

01:05:16.417 --> 01:05:20.564
TRAVIS: Yeah, this is also Matt Mercer, who had us
fight an entire thing, taking down damage the

01:05:20.564 --> 01:05:27.097
whole time while nothing was happening. I'll take
all three attacks at the window. Reckless.

01:05:27.097 --> 01:05:28.899
MATT: Go ahead and roll attack.

01:05:28.899 --> 01:05:31.881
TRAVIS: Natural 20.

01:05:31.881 --> 01:05:36.808
LAURA: Does that mean if I put an actual monster
