SAM: You don't know.

01:05:39.913 --> 01:05:45.999
TALIESIN: They'd have to think of it. I wouldn't
think of attacking the room, and he's designed to

01:05:45.999 --> 01:05:47.131
hurt rooms.

01:05:47.131 --> 01:05:48.795
LAURA: And he's designed to not think.

01:05:48.795 --> 01:05:50.394
MATT: He's designed to make terrible choices.

01:05:50.394 --> 01:05:55.877
TALIESIN: The room could collapse and squish him
like a bug, for all we know.

01:05:55.877 --> 01:05:59.737
TRAVIS: That critical is 55.

01:05:59.737 --> 01:06:03.388
MATT: So that's 110 points of damage with your
siege weaponry.

01:06:03.388 --> 01:06:08.006
LAURA: I'm so dead, you guys. He's going to pop
out!

01:06:08.006 --> 01:06:13.898
MATT: As you rear back for your second strike, you
bring your axe to go against this crystalline

01:06:13.898 --> 01:06:20.758
field, this layer that defends you from that. As
you slam it, the axe hits and you watch as it

01:06:20.758 --> 01:06:26.964
spider-cracks (cracking) all across, and the room
(rumbling) is now actively shaking. As you look

01:06:26.964 --> 01:06:30.455
around, you can see that the walls are starting to
crumble, and rocks begin to tumble, and you see

01:06:30.455 --> 01:06:33.124
what looks like a black void behind the cracks
that are opening.

01:06:33.124 --> 01:06:35.316
LAURA: Oh no, that could be really bad.

01:06:35.316 --> 01:06:39.399
MATT: You have a third attack, Grog. What are you
going to do, Mr. Raging?

01:06:39.399 --> 01:06:47.063
TALIESIN: Oh god, I love watching his brain
strain.

01:06:47.063 --> 01:06:49.576
MATT: What are you going to do?

01:06:49.576 --> 01:06:50.493
TRAVIS: Fuck it!

01:06:50.493 --> 01:06:52.209
LAURA: Oh shit!

01:06:52.209 --> 01:06:54.203
TRAVIS: Natural 20.

01:06:54.203 --> 01:06:55.853
MARISHA: No way. You are lying!

01:06:55.853 --> 01:06:57.022
TRAVIS: No, it's true.

01:06:57.022 --> 01:07:01.476
LAURA: What if you get sucked into a random void?
Then we can never defeat you.

01:07:01.476 --> 01:07:03.417
MATT: Roll some damage.

01:07:03.417 --> 01:07:07.893
MARISHA: If he gets sucked into a random void, I
imagine that would be considered defeat?

01:07:07.893 --> 01:07:10.589
MATT: Oh, he would be fucking dead.

01:07:10.589 --> 01:07:12.455
TRAVIS: 60 this time, so 120.

01:07:12.455 --> 01:07:21.099
MATT: So 120 points of damage. So Grog. You rear
back once more, and that little bit of doubt in

01:07:21.099 --> 01:07:25.737
the back of your brain, you quickly squash! As
your frenzied fury takes over, you see nothing but

01:07:25.737 --> 01:07:30.564
red, anger, and blood, as you rear back a third
time and (whack). As you slam it, you hear what

01:07:30.564 --> 01:07:36.047
sounds like a thousand windows shattering at once,
and all the walls suddenly collapse in towards

01:07:36.047 --> 01:07:41.061
you, rocketing and spiraling inward. It crushes
into your body as you're thrust forward as the

01:07:41.061 --> 01:07:44.647
crystalline structure ahead of you shatters and
pulls you through like a heavy vacuum.

01:07:44.647 --> 01:07:46.878
LAURA: Oh god, he's out!

01:07:46.946 --> 01:07:48.288
SAM: Or he's dead.

01:07:48.288 --> 01:07:55.430
MATT: You suffer 26 points of piercing and
bludgeoning damage.

01:07:55.430 --> 01:07:56.888
TRAVIS: Halved to 13?

01:07:56.888 --> 01:07:58.052
MATT: Halved to 13.

01:07:58.052 --> 01:07:59.216
SAM: That's not bad.

01:07:59.216 --> 01:08:01.214
TRAVIS: And imploded from the inside?

01:08:01.214 --> 01:08:05.468
MATT: And the necklace in front of you
(shattering) shatters off your chest, and you

01:08:05.468 --> 01:08:11.308
watch as a giant Grog, right there into the
hallway, right in front of you.

01:08:11.308 --> 01:08:15.605
MARISHA: Oh shit! So much just happened!

01:08:15.605 --> 01:08:19.872
TRAVIS: Because I reference Terminator 2 later...

01:08:19.872 --> 01:08:27.374
TALIESIN: You punched a hole through time and
space. Well done.

01:08:27.374 --> 01:08:35.072
MATT: Your necklace is gone. It is not functional
for the rest of this battle. I was not expecting

01:08:35.072 --> 01:08:37.420
you to attack the inside of the wall.

01:08:37.420 --> 01:08:39.876
TRAVIS: I was just going to do it because he's an
idiot, but that really worked!

01:08:39.876 --> 01:08:43.670
MATT: All righty! That ends your turn, Grog.

01:08:43.670 --> 01:08:44.514
TRAVIS: Yeah!

01:08:44.514 --> 01:08:45.569
MATT: Keyleth, you're up.

01:08:45.569 --> 01:08:46.924
LAURA: I was going to release you!

01:08:46.924 --> 01:08:48.358
SAM: In acid!

01:08:48.358 --> 01:09:00.298
MARISHA: Okay. I'm going to turn around and be
like (screams, booming) on both of these guys. I'm

01:09:00.298 --> 01:09:12.659
going to move into Vex's space and then attack
Grog. (bam, bam)

01:09:12.659 --> 01:09:15.774
MATT: Go for it. You're technically occupying
Vex's space, right there.

01:09:15.774 --> 01:09:16.890
MARISHA: Correct.

01:09:16.890 --> 01:09:18.793
MATT: So you attack.

01:09:18.793 --> 01:09:21.718
MARISHA: 15.

01:09:21.718 --> 01:09:23.013
TRAVIS: Misses.

01:09:23.013 --> 01:09:30.457
MARISHA: Second one, much better. That hits. 16
plus six is 22.

01:09:30.457 --> 01:09:35.934
MATT: 22? That hits, yeah. So go ahead and roll
damage against Vex. Vex, you also catch fire.

01:09:35.934 --> 01:09:39.266
MARISHA: Oh, I'm attacking Grog.

01:09:39.266 --> 01:09:43.790
MATT: Oh, Grog! I misunderstood, sorry. So Grog,
you catch fire. Flames are just (whoosh).

01:09:43.790 --> 01:09:47.994
SAM: You're having a weird six seconds of your
life right now.

01:09:47.994 --> 01:09:57.732
TRAVIS: I know! (panting, warp sound effect,
screaming) Hulk angry!

01:09:57.732 --> 01:10:00.546
MARISHA: That's 20 fire damage.

01:10:00.546 --> 01:10:04.385
MATT: So you take 20 points of fire damage,
reduced to ten, and you're on fire. And you will

01:10:04.385 --> 01:10:08.292
remain on fire, taking 1d10 fire damage every
round, until you spend an action to put it out.

01:10:08.292 --> 01:10:09.579
SAM: But it looks cool.

01:10:09.579 --> 01:10:14.580
MATT: But it looks cool. All right, and because
you moved into Vex's space, Vex, you also catch

01:10:14.580 --> 01:10:21.291
fire automatically. Does she immediately take the
1d10 damage for occupying someone's space?

