01:40:57.654 --> 01:41:00.834
LAURA: Oh right. Okay, wait. That's an additional
4d8.

01:41:00.834 --> 01:41:07.524
TALIESIN: Shit. Yeah, no. I'm fucked, anyway.

01:41:07.524 --> 01:41:09.112
SAM: Maybe not.

01:41:09.112 --> 01:41:12.683
TRAVIS: Hey, man. Better to be done by your lover
than by me. I left that action surge out.

01:41:12.683 --> 01:41:17.215
TALIESIN: Oh, I have another action surge that I
didn't-- I was hoping.

01:41:17.215 --> 01:41:26.661
LAURA: (adding) 38, plus six lightning damage.

01:41:26.661 --> 01:41:34.215
TALIESIN: 38 plus six lightning damage? And then
I'm going to take... ugh, this is the worst I've

01:41:34.215 --> 01:41:39.968
ever rolled in my life. 38 plus six lightning. I'm
going to bring that down to 25 points of damage.

01:41:39.968 --> 01:41:41.206
MATT: From?

01:41:41.206 --> 01:41:47.886
TALIESIN: From the Gloves of Missile Snaring. So
38 down to 25. Plus six lightning damage?

01:41:47.886 --> 01:41:50.264
Still alive.

01:41:50.264 --> 01:41:56.397
MATT: As you're on the wall, you feel the sense,
this burning in your ears, and you glance up just

01:41:56.397 --> 01:42:01.503
as you watch an arrow (arrow sound) come towards
you and as it bursts open, this series of tendrils

01:42:01.503 --> 01:42:05.933
of vines, you reach over and grab and stop the
arrow, somewhat, before it pierces into you, but

01:42:05.933 --> 01:42:10.491
you still manage to pull it back and the vines
begin to ensnare around you. Go ahead and roll a

01:42:10.491 --> 01:42:15.891
strength saving throw, I believe?

01:42:15.891 --> 01:42:17.055
TALIESIN: 16?

01:42:17.088 --> 01:42:20.401
MATT: DC 17. They (whoosh) wrap around you and you
find yourself--

01:42:20.401 --> 01:42:24.000
TALIESIN: Actually, this is better. I'm so sorry.
Strength saving throw, 22.

01:42:24.000 --> 01:42:29.160
MATT: That does succeed. So as they wrap around
you, you (strained grunting) and burst off of them

01:42:29.160 --> 01:42:33.730
and the arrow breaks out and they all turn gray
and wither into dust as they hit the ground.

01:42:33.730 --> 01:42:36.553
LAURA: You're so strong, darling. I'm so
impressed.

01:42:36.553 --> 01:42:38.598
Right as I throw another arrow at him.

01:42:38.598 --> 01:42:41.742
(laughter)

01:42:41.742 --> 01:42:43.884
LAURA: That's a 25 to hit.

01:42:43.884 --> 01:42:45.517
MATT and TALIESIN: That hits.

01:42:45.517 --> 01:42:49.745
LAURA: I'm going to do another... no, I'm not. I'm
not going to do a bramble shot on him. I'm just

01:42:49.745 --> 01:42:50.961
going to do a regular shot.

01:42:50.961 --> 01:42:52.426
TALIESIN: No, it's smart.

01:42:52.426 --> 01:42:54.166
LAURA: Well, yeah, he's taking half damage.

01:42:54.166 --> 01:42:56.871
TALIESIN: I'm bleeding out. I'm just blood.

01:42:56.871 --> 01:43:00.830
LAURA: Oh wait, do you only get to use the catch
once?

01:43:00.830 --> 01:43:04.292
TALIESIN: Once per turn. It's a reaction.

01:43:04.292 --> 01:43:10.821
LAURA: 12, 14, 16 plus six lightning damage.

01:43:10.821 --> 01:43:12.219
TALIESIN: I'm out.

01:43:12.219 --> 01:43:21.603
MATT: You fall unconscious and off the wall,
hitting the ground. You take three points of

01:43:21.603 --> 01:43:24.489
bludgeoning damage as you hit, which is an
immediate failed death save.

01:43:24.489 --> 01:43:25.918
TALIESIN: Are we doing death saves?

01:43:25.918 --> 01:43:27.471
MATT: Oh yeah, that's part of this.

01:43:27.471 --> 01:43:30.809
MARISHA: So you could theoretically recover and
come back.

01:43:30.809 --> 01:43:34.790
MATT: Yeah, if you roll a natural 20 on your death
save. It's happened before.

01:43:34.790 --> 01:43:43.492
LAURA: Fuck, okay. Those are my two attacks, so
can I fly down to the ground behind the

01:43:43.492 --> 01:43:50.885
building... actually, they're all over on the
other side. I'm going to drop down where I am.

01:43:50.885 --> 01:43:53.713
MATT: Okay. Drop down to the roof?

01:43:53.713 --> 01:44:02.337
LAURA: Yeah, to the roof. And I'm going to lay
down on the roof and use my bonus action to hide.

01:44:02.337 --> 01:44:07.432
MATT: Okay, you lay down on the roof, using your
bonus action to hide.

01:44:07.432 --> 01:44:10.812
Go ahead and roll a stealth check.

01:44:10.812 --> 01:44:12.121
LAURA: 27.

01:44:12.121 --> 01:44:17.189
MATT: 27. As far as you know, no one has any idea
where the hell you are. All right, that ends your

01:44:17.189 --> 01:44:18.892
turn. Grog, you're up.

01:44:18.892 --> 01:44:23.838
TRAVIS: I see Vex...

01:44:23.838 --> 01:44:25.592
MATT: You watch her (descending noise).

01:44:25.592 --> 01:44:32.369
TRAVIS: But she was shooting at my quarry. I turn
the corner towards where Percy is.

01:44:32.369 --> 01:44:38.723
MATT: As you lumber around, you go and see his
unconscious body there, on the ground.

01:44:38.815 --> 01:44:46.643
TRAVIS: (gasps) Percy von Fredrickstein de blah,
skittles and balls and ass. What happened?

01:44:46.643 --> 01:44:49.759
TALIESIN: He burns an action doing this, I
assume.

01:44:49.759 --> 01:44:52.234
(laughter)

01:44:52.234 --> 01:44:56.233
TRAVIS: Spin the hammer, right down on his head.

01:44:56.233 --> 01:45:03.172
MATT: Okay, you move in. That's ten more feet. Go
ahead and roll, with advantage.

01:45:03.172 --> 01:45:09.801
TRAVIS: (laughing) That's a 32.

01:45:09.801 --> 01:45:12.724
MATT: All right. It's an auto-crit because it was
within five feet. How do you want to do this?

01:45:12.799 --> 01:45:22.276
TRAVIS: I start to swing down. Did he get new
glasses? I take them. (heavy impact)

01:45:22.276 --> 01:45:28.663
(laughter)

01:45:28.663 --> 01:45:32.520
MATT: The whole face caves in as the hammer
scatters him like a Gallagher watermelon across

01:45:32.520 --> 01:45:33.942
the stone floor.

01:45:33.942 --> 01:45:36.315
TRAVIS: Oh, I can see very well.

01:45:36.315 --> 01:45:38.209
(laughter)

01:45:38.209 --> 01:45:41.381
MATT: Percival is no more. First to fall.

01:45:41.381 --> 01:45:43.664
TRAVIS: How much speed did I use?

01:45:43.664 --> 01:45:49.699
MATT: Five, ten, 15, 20.

01:45:49.699 --> 01:45:51.272
TRAVIS: 20.

01:45:51.272 --> 01:45:54.829
MARISHA: And the sound of the first cannon.

01:45:54.829 --> 01:46:01.343
TRAVIS: Can I use my bonus action to leap, with
the feral leaping, 20 feet toward the tower?

01:46:01.343 --> 01:46:03.124
MATT: Toward the tower this way?

01:46:03.124 --> 01:46:04.290
TRAVIS: Entrance, down.

01:46:04.290 --> 01:46:07.115
MATT: Yeah, if you want to. Go ahead and roll for
that.

01:46:07.115 --> 01:46:14.104
TRAVIS: 21.

01:46:14.104 --> 01:46:19.672
MATT: You land (grunt, impact noise) right toward
the base.

01:46:19.672 --> 01:46:23.061
TRAVIS: Can I use the remainder of my speed to run
up the tower?

01:46:23.061 --> 01:46:24.744
MARISHA: And he's still on fire, right?

01:46:24.744 --> 01:46:27.489
TRAVIS: Yep. Oh, I need to take the fire damage.

01:46:27.489 --> 01:46:31.264
MATT: That's true. Last round, or just this one?

01:46:31.264 --> 01:46:33.654
TRAVIS: Just this one. I took it last time.

01:46:33.654 --> 01:46:36.121
MATT: That's five fire damage, reduced to two.

01:46:36.121 --> 01:46:39.239
TRAVIS: Two. On fire.

01:46:39.239 --> 01:46:44.792
MATT: And you disappear into the center of the
tower.

01:46:44.792 --> 01:46:46.696
TRAVIS: 20 feet in?

01:46:46.696 --> 01:46:48.452
MATT: You get partway up the stairs.

01:46:48.452 --> 01:46:49.646
TRAVIS: Is it a winding thing?

01:46:49.646 --> 01:46:54.256
MATT: Yeah, it's a spiral staircase. All right,
that ends your turn, Grog. Keyleth?

01:46:54.256 --> 01:46:58.402
MARISHA: Okay, I saw Vex shooting Percy?

01:46:58.402 --> 01:47:03.375
MATT: No, you were inside the cusp of this
building the entire time. Glancing around there,

01:47:03.375 --> 01:47:08.366
you saw her up there, and make a perception
check.

01:47:08.366 --> 01:47:19.911
MARISHA: Okay. 20. No, 21.

01:47:19.911 --> 01:47:26.656
MATT: 21. You got the gist. You watched her
descend, but you have no idea directly where she

01:47:26.656 --> 01:47:29.148
is. You know she's somewhere in this area.

01:47:29.148 --> 01:47:32.874
MARISHA: Okay. So I don't see anyone?

01:47:32.874 --> 01:47:36.995
MATT: You know where she is. If you have an area
something you want to do, you could probably hit

01:47:36.995 --> 01:47:41.017
her, but you can't aim a specific attack directly
at her because you can't see her.

01:47:41.017 --> 01:48:08.522
MARISHA: Okay. I am going to start by moving my
fire ball. Jeez. There's not a lot I can do. I saw

01:48:08.522 --> 01:48:10.914
Grog run by, as well, correct?

01:48:10.914 --> 01:48:16.658
MATT: You saw Grog run by this way, and that's the
last you saw. And you know that Vex is somewhere

01:48:16.658 --> 01:48:21.013
in this area. What do you want to do?

01:48:21.013 --> 01:48:26.370
MARISHA: I'm going to move out and around on this
side, my movement over here.

01:48:26.370 --> 01:48:28.595
MATT: You're there.

01:48:28.595 --> 01:48:35.925
MARISHA: I'm going to go ahead and use my bonus
action to heal a little bit more. Actually, no,

01:48:35.925 --> 01:48:40.807
can I use my action to heal like last time and use
my bonus action to move my sphere?

01:48:40.807 --> 01:48:50.302
MATT: Sure. Yeah, okay, go for it. Technically...
yeah, it's fine.

01:48:50.302 --> 01:49:00.825
MARISHA: I'm going to do 1st-level. Five. Okay.
And then I'm going to move my sphere right in

01:49:00.825 --> 01:49:02.600
front of the doorway.

01:49:02.600 --> 01:49:03.954
MATT: 30 feet for the sphere?

01:49:03.954 --> 01:49:05.936
MARISHA: Yeah, however far it can go.

01:49:05.936 --> 01:49:11.455
MATT: There, that's as far as it can get right
there. Okay, that ends your turn, Keyleth?

01:49:11.455 --> 01:49:18.677
MARISHA: Do I have any more movement? I'll pop
back in the building a little bit, and that's it.

01:49:18.677 --> 01:49:21.631
MATT: All righty. Taryon, your turn.

01:49:21.631 --> 01:49:25.683
TRAVIS: How many rounds is this? Four? Five?

01:49:25.683 --> 01:49:26.795
LAURA: This is the sixth round.

01:49:26.795 --> 01:49:28.067
SAM: This is the fifth round.

01:49:28.067 --> 01:49:30.172
LAURA: This is the fifth round. After this will be
the sixth.

01:49:30.172 --> 01:49:48.273
SAM: Invisibility. And I want to fly out of the
sphere and to a vantage point of your choosing, so

01:49:48.273 --> 01:49:55.560
no one knows where I am, somewhere between 20 and
40 feet high, maybe towards the center-ish of the

01:49:55.560 --> 01:49:58.165
game field. Up to you where.

01:49:58.165 --> 01:50:00.678
MATT: Okay, I know where you are. That's your
turn?

01:50:00.678 --> 01:50:01.668
SAM: Yes.

01:50:01.668 --> 01:50:02.915
MATT: Okay, Taryon.

01:50:02.915 --> 01:50:04.259
TRAVIS: Do you know where?

01:50:04.259 --> 01:50:07.173
SAM: No, I don't want to know where I am so you
don't know where I am.

01:50:07.173 --> 01:50:08.480
LAURA: It's smart.

01:50:08.480 --> 01:50:13.408
(laughter)

01:50:13.408 --> 01:50:18.338
MATT: No longer Percy's turn. So with that, the
braziers--

01:50:18.338 --> 01:50:22.653
SAM: And Matt. Away from the things that blow up.
Was that understood?

01:50:22.653 --> 01:50:29.014
MATT: Right, yes. And all the braziers flare up.
Don't affect anybody. That brings us to Vex.

01:50:29.014 --> 01:50:35.948
LAURA: I'm going to take off from the roof and try
to make it to the opposite tower.

01:50:35.948 --> 01:50:38.964
MATT: The opposite tower, flying over here?

01:50:38.964 --> 01:50:39.917
LAURA: Yeah.

01:50:39.917 --> 01:50:42.314
MATT: You make your way there.

01:50:42.314 --> 01:50:44.584
LAURA: Can I see anything?

01:50:44.584 --> 01:50:52.478
MATT: Make a perception check.

01:50:52.732 --> 01:50:55.600
LAURA: 20.

01:50:55.600 --> 01:50:59.620
MATT: Yeah, you see the flickering flames of
Keyleth within the inside, in the very cusp of

01:50:59.620 --> 01:51:02.216
this. She has three-quarters cover, but you have
sharpshooter, so you ignore that.

01:51:02.216 --> 01:51:09.498
LAURA: Well, then I'll try to hit her. I'm going to
attack her! That's a 27.

01:51:09.498 --> 01:51:11.020
MATT and MARISHA: That hits.

01:51:11.020 --> 01:51:26.449
LAURA: Eight plus five is-- no, is it? No. 13? 15,
plus four lightning damage.

01:51:26.449 --> 01:51:29.063
And then I'm going to do it again.

01:51:29.063 --> 01:51:31.679
MATT: 17 points of damage.

01:51:31.679 --> 01:51:42.400
LAURA: I'm going to do a bramble shot on her,
because I only did the one. 25 to hit.

01:51:42.400 --> 01:51:46.175
MATT: 25 to hit? That hits. Damage?

01:51:46.175 --> 01:52:05.097
LAURA: (counting) 32, plus three lightning
damage.

01:52:05.097 --> 01:52:07.884
TRAVIS: 35, damn.

01:52:07.884 --> 01:52:13.740
MATT: As the brambles wrap around her, the flames
burn them away. She's immune to being restrained.

01:52:13.740 --> 01:52:22.400
LAURA: Yeah, I figured. I bet Tary's up here, but
I don't know that. I'm going to use my bonus

01:52:22.400 --> 01:52:30.332
action to hide. I was hidden at the beginning of
the turn, but I'm assuming my movement took me out

01:52:30.332 --> 01:52:36.309
of hiding. Can I use my skirmisher's stealth to
choose a quarry to stay hidden? Or I have to be

01:52:36.309 --> 01:52:37.860
hidden at the top of the turn?

01:52:37.860 --> 01:52:42.786
MATT: At this point, yeah. We're skirting a line,
here, of watching you go up and land. You aren't

01:52:42.786 --> 01:52:49.201
amongst trees in a forest. It's easy to see where
you are, vaguely.

01:52:49.201 --> 01:52:50.848
LAURA: Okay, I'm going to hide.

01:52:50.922 --> 01:52:53.815
MATT: Roll a stealth check.

01:52:53.815 --> 01:52:56.255
LAURA: Only 18.

01:52:56.255 --> 01:52:59.256
MATT: Okay, good to know. That ends Vex's turn.
Grog!

01:52:59.256 --> 01:53:09.060
TRAVIS: Right. I don't see any immediate chests in
this big tower, right? It's just a stairwell?

01:53:09.060 --> 01:53:13.500
MATT: No, it's just stairwell. Like when you went
through the other one, it's empty, more of a

01:53:13.500 --> 01:53:17.310
gaining of ground and/or protective space.

01:53:17.310 --> 01:53:24.392
TRAVIS: All right. Live and let die,
motherfuckers! Can I run out of the tower,

01:53:24.392 --> 01:53:27.518
straight towards the pool of acid?

01:53:27.518 --> 01:53:35.106
MATT: You got ten feet in, so ten feet out. You still
have 40 at the doorway. There's a Flaming Sphere

01:53:35.106 --> 01:53:37.148
there, which you're like, "oh, avoid!"

01:53:37.148 --> 01:53:42.170
TRAVIS: Yeah, I'm aiming to try and make my way to
this structure.

01:53:42.170 --> 01:53:48.762
MATT: 25, 30, 35, 40. You're just stepping over
the corpse of Trinket.

01:53:48.762 --> 01:53:50.336
TRAVIS: Lovely.

01:53:50.336 --> 01:53:54.742
LAURA: Oh, I forgot he's just unconscious. He's
not dead yet. I haven't been making saving throws

01:53:54.742 --> 01:53:57.660
for him.

01:53:57.660 --> 01:54:01.177
MATT: He's doing okay for now. Grog, that's your
movement.

01:54:01.244 --> 01:54:10.601
TRAVIS: I raise my hammer as I get to Trinket. I
don't give a shit about Trinket.

01:54:10.601 --> 01:54:17.238
What square am I on?

01:54:17.238 --> 01:54:24.355
MATT: You're technically right here. You have your
action, still. You can dash if you want to get all

01:54:24.355 --> 01:54:27.150
the way there, or you can attack something in the
vicinity. What do you want to do?

01:54:27.150 --> 01:54:31.882
TRAVIS: Yeah, I'll dash.

01:54:31.882 --> 01:54:45.955
MATT: (counting) You get inside here and see a
small chest by the doorway there.

01:54:45.955 --> 01:54:47.681
TRAVIS: Can I move to the chest?

01:54:47.681 --> 01:54:50.264
MATT: You can move to the chest, but it'll take an
action to open it.

01:54:50.264 --> 01:54:54.609
TRAVIS: Can I use my action surge, which I have
not used, to open the chest?

01:54:54.609 --> 01:55:01.910
MATT: Yes, you can. You do. You open it up, and
there is a potion bottle within it. So you acquire

01:55:01.910 --> 01:55:04.788
the potion. You open the chest and you grab the
potion.

01:55:04.788 --> 01:55:08.056
TRAVIS: Right, and I can't do anything else? Can I
consume it?

01:55:08.056 --> 01:55:09.848
MATT: You have your bonus action, still, right?

01:55:09.848 --> 01:55:12.796
TRAVIS: Yeah! That's right. Chug-a-lug, bitches.

01:55:12.796 --> 01:55:14.264
MATT: So 4d4 plus four.

01:55:14.264 --> 01:55:18.627
TRAVIS: Gimme some squares. No, 4d4. I need some
triangles.

01:55:18.627 --> 01:55:21.619
MATT: You also take six points of fire damage,
reduced to three.

01:55:21.619 --> 01:55:25.363
Because you're doing this while on fire.

01:55:25.363 --> 01:55:38.746
TRAVIS: Yeah. 4d4 plus four. 14 points. That's my
turn.

01:55:38.746 --> 01:55:40.772
MAT: Okay, Grog's done. Keyleth?

01:55:40.772 --> 01:55:48.097
MARISHA: Okay. (grunts) Going to go ahead and drop
my fire elemental form. It's looking pretty rough

01:55:48.097 --> 01:55:54.299
now. Hope I don't fuck that up. And I'm going to
peek around the corner and I can see

01:55:54.299 --> 01:55:56.432
Vex a little up on the tower.

01:55:56.496 --> 01:55:58.351
MATT: Make a perception check.

01:55:58.351 --> 01:56:02.936
MARISHA: Don't fuck me, Gil, don't fuck me! Oh,
that's good! 29.

01:56:02.936 --> 01:56:07.268
MATT: You glance up the tower, and you see just
the edge of Vex trying to hide around the

01:56:07.268 --> 01:56:10.615
stonework. You see her feather and the edge of her
hair, and you see her right up on the top.

01:56:10.615 --> 01:56:17.524
MARISHA: I'll be like, (yelling) your blue feather
is very pretty against the stonework!

01:56:17.524 --> 01:56:19.194
LAURA: We have earrings, dear.

01:56:19.194 --> 01:56:21.522
(laughter)

01:56:21.522 --> 01:56:28.438
MARISHA: I yell it through the earring, and it
deafens her a little bit. (yelps) Ow, feedback.

01:56:28.509 --> 01:56:33.227
LAURA: Do I hear Tary go (yelps) anywhere?

01:56:33.227 --> 01:56:34.299
MATT: No.

01:56:34.299 --> 01:56:39.661
MARISHA: And I'm going to take my Spire of
Conflux, and just to be sure, I'm going to call a

01:56:39.661 --> 01:56:47.883
Fire Storm down and blanket the tower, and I want
to go down a little bit. So here's what I want.

01:56:47.883 --> 01:56:52.425
I want this.

01:56:52.425 --> 01:56:58.287
MATT: The Fire Storm down the side? How many cubes
is it?

01:56:58.287 --> 01:57:01.890
MARISHA: Rain fire down everywhere.

01:57:01.890 --> 01:57:09.189
MATT: That's nasty. Okay, Fire Storm. Ten ten-foot
cubes.

01:57:09.189 --> 01:57:16.589
MARISHA: Because I don't know where Tary is. I
haven't seen him in a while.

01:57:16.589 --> 01:57:21.449
MATT: You could even get to Grog, if you wanted
to.

01:57:21.449 --> 01:57:23.448
MARISHA: It's a fire waterfall.

01:57:23.448 --> 01:57:29.741
MATT: Yeah, it is. It's very Minecraft. (fire
noises) All right, I need you to go ahead and make

01:57:29.741 --> 01:57:33.283
a dexterity saving throw, Vex. And Marisha, roll
7d10.

01:57:33.283 --> 01:57:35.237
LAURA: Oh my god.

01:57:35.237 --> 01:57:36.839
TRAVIS: 7d10?!

01:57:36.839 --> 01:57:39.484
MATT: Yeah, that's the damage of Fire Storm, man.

01:57:39.484 --> 01:57:40.796
LAURA: 20.

01:57:40.796 --> 01:57:42.241
