02:32:53.648 --> 02:32:58.335
acid breath. 60-foot line, five-foot wide.

02:32:58.335 --> 02:33:00.129
SAM: You're trashed.

02:33:00.129 --> 02:33:03.417
TRAVIS: Fire elemental, back to Keyleth, into a
dragon?

02:33:03.417 --> 02:33:04.730
LAURA: Come on.

02:33:04.730 --> 02:33:07.991
MATT: To be fair, you guys focused on each other
for most of this fight.

02:33:07.991 --> 02:33:10.036
TRAVIS: That's true.

02:33:10.036 --> 02:33:13.700
MATT: I need you to make a dexterity saving throw,
Grog.

02:33:13.700 --> 02:33:19.857
TRAVIS: Thank you. Thank you, sir. May I have
another? 17.

02:33:19.857 --> 02:33:24.597
MATT: That does not succeed. Keyleth, I need you
to roll your 12d8 acid damage

02:33:24.597 --> 02:33:26.591
that Grog's about to take.

02:33:26.591 --> 02:33:30.383
LAURA: Oh, are you immune to acid damage?

02:33:30.383 --> 02:33:31.539
TRAVIS: No.

02:33:31.539 --> 02:33:33.056
MATT: Nor resistant.

02:33:33.056 --> 02:33:42.430
MARISHA: I'll roll five and then I'll roll five
more. Actually, give me one more and I'll roll

02:33:42.430 --> 02:33:47.260
twice. Get that out of there.

02:33:47.260 --> 02:33:50.968
TALIESIN: And ones you reroll, right?

02:33:50.968 --> 02:33:52.353
MARISHA: Yeah.

02:33:52.353 --> 02:33:55.422
TALIESIN: (cackles)

02:33:55.422 --> 02:34:06.600
MARISHA: 16, plus let's do these two twos, which
