roll?

02:59:38.704 --> 02:59:39.629
MARISHA: 15.

02:59:39.629 --> 02:59:45.839
MATT: 15. So you take 16 points of lightning
damage. Go ahead and roll a constitution check.

02:59:45.839 --> 02:59:48.023
MARISHA: A lot. I'm good.

02:59:48.023 --> 02:59:49.314
MATT: Okay.

02:59:49.314 --> 02:59:52.644
LAURA: That's a failed death save for me.

02:59:52.644 --> 02:59:57.646
MATT: And... yeah. How many have you lost now?

02:59:57.646 --> 03:00:00.578
LAURA: That's two fails.

03:00:00.578 --> 03:00:02.231
TRAVIS: What is the point?

03:00:02.231 --> 03:00:05.030
MATT: Now it's your turn. Go ahead and roll
again.

03:00:05.030 --> 03:00:11.148
LAURA: Well, all right. One!

03:00:11.148 --> 03:00:18.961
MATT: And with that, we'll say from a narrative
standpoint, as the lightning sparks out and it

03:00:18.961 --> 03:00:22.452
hits Keyleth in her dragon form, she falls back
and her back foot (squelch)

03:00:22.452 --> 03:00:27.111
accidentally smears Vex.

03:00:27.111 --> 03:00:31.244
TALIESIN: That's going to be hard to clean up.

03:00:31.244 --> 03:00:34.025
LAURA: No fate dice for us, Percy.

03:00:34.025 --> 03:00:40.547
MATT: All right, so that's the end of Vex's turn.
Grog, you're up.

03:00:40.547 --> 03:00:44.315
TRAVIS: I pull out the rest of the-- no, I run up
to the top of the tower.

03:00:44.315 --> 03:00:46.952
TALIESIN: Fear?

03:00:46.952 --> 03:00:50.892
MARISHA: He's immune to fear because barbarian and
raging.

03:00:50.892 --> 03:00:52.763
TRAVIS: I ain't scared.

03:00:52.763 --> 03:00:54.070
MARISHA: He ain't scared.

03:00:54.070 --> 03:01:03.275
TRAVIS: It's absurd. And then she has all of her
hit points left.

03:01:03.275 --> 03:01:09.401
MATT: So Grog, you get up to the top of the hatch
and you come out and you're right there next to

03:01:09.401 --> 03:01:12.681
your goliath friend, in the face of this big
dragon. What are you going to do?

03:01:12.681 --> 03:01:17.580
TRAVIS: I'm going to rush up to the giant red
dragon and go: Yo, Wilfred. This is how it's done,

03:01:17.580 --> 03:01:22.657
lad. And I do all three attacks, reckless, at the
fucking dragon.

03:01:22.657 --> 03:01:24.206
MATT: Okay. Go for it.

03:01:24.206 --> 03:01:26.944
SAM: Reckless? You could kill the dragon in one
move.

03:01:26.944 --> 03:01:29.964
TRAVIS: I don't think so. That's a 32?

03:01:29.964 --> 03:01:35.714
MARISHA: To hit? Yeah. He could take me down.

03:01:35.714 --> 03:01:37.614
TRAVIS: 24 on the first one.

03:01:37.614 --> 03:01:39.007
MARISHA: Damage?

03:01:39.007 --> 03:01:43.131
MATT: Before you roll damage on the next one, roll
another constitution saving throw for

03:01:43.131 --> 03:01:45.612
concentration. Beat a 12.

03:01:45.612 --> 03:01:46.472
MARISHA: Yeah.

03:01:46.472 --> 03:01:47.517
MATT: Okay.

03:01:47.517 --> 03:01:49.520
TRAVIS: Natural 20.

03:01:49.520 --> 03:01:52.946
TALIESIN: You've had a few of those tonight.

03:01:52.946 --> 03:02:05.221
TRAVIS: Okay, so that was a nine, so 25. That was
nine on the die.

03:02:05.221 --> 03:02:11.866
MATT: You rolled a nine on the die. This is the
damage.

03:02:11.866 --> 03:02:13.838
MARISHA: Oh, right.

03:02:13.838 --> 03:02:17.409
MATT: So 18, plus your modifier.

03:02:17.409 --> 03:02:20.718
TRAVIS: So that's 34.

03:02:20.718 --> 03:02:23.470
MATT: Plus two additional dice for the weapon.

03:02:23.470 --> 03:02:33.305
TRAVIS: That's right, yeah. Ten, plus a three.
47.

03:02:33.305 --> 03:02:34.374
MARISHA: Total?

03:02:34.374 --> 03:02:39.971
MATT: 47 points of damage to you. Roll another
constitution saving throw. You have to beat a 23.

03:02:39.971 --> 03:02:48.110
MARISHA: As long as I roll over--

03:02:48.110 --> 03:02:49.310
MATT: Constitution.

03:02:49.310 --> 03:02:50.672
MARISHA: Oh, constitution?

03:02:50.672 --> 03:02:52.875
MATT: It's not wisdom. It's constitution for
these.

03:02:52.875 --> 03:02:54.940
LAURA: Have you been adding your wisdom modifier
this whole time?

03:02:54.940 --> 03:03:05.274
MARISHA: My constitution's all right. I've been
rolling over the minimum, anyway. No. Nope.

03:03:05.274 --> 03:03:07.444
MATT: Keyleth's form drops.

03:03:07.444 --> 03:03:09.262
SAM: Oh shit!

03:03:09.262 --> 03:03:21.124
MATT: The spell drops, losing concentration. Her
form reverts into regular Keyleth again. It wasn't

03:03:21.124 --> 03:03:25.352
damage over. There's Keyleth in front of you. You
still have your third attack.

03:03:25.352 --> 03:03:28.045
TRAVIS: I definitely think about kicking her off
the top of the tower.

03:03:28.045 --> 03:03:29.819
SAM: Of course you do.

03:03:29.819 --> 03:03:34.885
TRAVIS: I think the attack is better. Yep.
Reckless.

03:03:34.885 --> 03:03:37.877
SAM: So many menu options.

03:03:37.877 --> 03:03:43.503
TRAVIS: That hits. 33.

03:03:43.503 --> 03:03:45.451
MATT: Okay. Go ahead and roll damage.

03:03:45.451 --> 03:03:46.903
MARISHA: Why were you like, ugh?
You wanted a critical?

03:03:46.903 --> 03:03:50.657
TALIESIN: Don't be greedy.

03:03:50.657 --> 03:03:53.268
TRAVIS: I know. 27.

03:03:53.268 --> 03:03:54.938
MARISHA: Damage total?

03:03:54.938 --> 03:04:01.748
MATT: 27 damage to you, and your friend next to
you, who's no longer frightened because you're no

03:04:01.748 --> 03:04:03.169
longer a dragon.

03:04:03.169 --> 03:04:05.143
MARISHA: He doesn't get to attack, does he?

03:04:05.143 --> 03:04:10.825
MATT: Yeah, he does. He attacks on your turn. He
