do it as a lower-level spell?

03:28:46.859 --> 03:28:48.407
SAM: Shenanigans.

03:28:48.407 --> 03:28:52.681
MATT: He's basically sacrificing a high-level
spell to cast a lower-level spell that doesn't get

03:28:52.681 --> 03:28:54.454
any benefit from being sacrificed.

03:28:54.454 --> 03:29:00.998
TRAVIS: First wisdom save. Goddamn, the fucking--
17?

03:29:00.998 --> 03:29:02.722
SAM: That's my DC.

03:29:02.722 --> 03:29:04.589
MATT: First attack, you get through.

03:29:04.589 --> 03:29:07.346
SAM: Where are you?

03:29:07.346 --> 03:29:08.955
MATT: He moved right under here.

03:29:08.955 --> 03:29:10.597
TALIESIN: He's right under you.

03:29:10.597 --> 03:29:11.932
SAM: But I'm over the acid!

03:29:11.932 --> 03:29:14.953
MARISHA: If you land in the acid, dude--

03:29:14.953 --> 03:29:17.084
LAURA: If he knocks you off your broom?

03:29:17.084 --> 03:29:19.612
TRAVIS: It's a 37 to hit.

03:29:19.612 --> 03:29:24.060
LAURA: Did he get knocked off his broom? He
doesn't have the same things that I have.

03:29:24.132 --> 03:29:28.343
TRAVIS: 24 on the first hit, for damage.

03:29:28.343 --> 03:29:32.789
TALIESIN: I don't think we ever built a safety net
into his broom.

03:29:32.789 --> 03:29:37.657
MATT: No, but he's not being knocked-- if it was
an attack that pushed or did anything to affect

03:29:37.657 --> 03:29:41.111
his movement or yank him, then it would become an
issue. Just doing damage won't do anything.

03:29:41.111 --> 03:29:46.663
TRAVIS: Oh, 26?

03:29:46.663 --> 03:29:49.540
MATT: The same things that would knock him off the
broom would knock you off the broom. It would just

03:29:49.540 --> 03:29:51.588
mean the broom stays attached to you.

03:29:51.588 --> 03:30:02.750
TRAVIS: 22. Natural 19. Son of a bitch. A
million.

03:30:02.750 --> 03:30:04.455
SAM: Sure.

03:30:04.455 --> 03:30:07.161
MARISHA: I love that he's getting so cranky about
rolling natural 19s.

03:30:07.263 --> 03:30:14.858
TRAVIS: 19 points of damage. I mean, after six
rolls, you'd hope so.

03:30:14.858 --> 03:30:17.653
MATT: You made a save on each of those rolls?

03:30:17.653 --> 03:30:22.139
TRAVIS: I am so sorry. I thought after I got
through the first one it just dispelled it.

03:30:22.139 --> 03:30:23.582
MATT: Nope!

03:30:23.582 --> 03:30:26.473
TRAVIS: The first one was a 24, I think?

03:30:26.473 --> 03:30:27.538
MATT: Yes.

03:30:27.538 --> 03:30:28.888
TRAVIS: So you need to erase--

03:30:28.888 --> 03:30:30.901
MATT: Well, you have to roll saves for the next
two.

03:30:30.901 --> 03:30:37.503
TRAVIS: Oh, okay. I probably won't get through
him, though. 15?

03:30:37.503 --> 03:30:38.658
SAM: Nope.

03:30:38.658 --> 03:30:39.831
TRAVIS: 15.

03:30:39.831 --> 03:30:41.954
MATT: All right, so the last two attacks do no
damage.

03:30:41.954 --> 03:30:44.724
SAM: I live to see another day.

03:30:44.724 --> 03:30:47.281
TRAVIS: I'm sorry. I thought it dispelled it.

03:30:47.281 --> 03:30:48.830
MARISHA: Or 15 more seconds.

03:30:48.830 --> 03:30:56.249
SAM: Jesus Christ. I know that he takes acid
damage, right?

03:30:56.249 --> 03:30:58.760
MATT: Yes. He doesn't appear to be resistant to
acid damage.

03:30:58.760 --> 03:31:07.682
SAM: Okay, then I will throw acid at him. In
the face!

03:31:07.682 --> 03:31:11.237
MATT: Two-Face style.

03:31:11.237 --> 03:31:15.532
SAM: Yeah, the acid drop. It's a dex save.

03:31:15.532 --> 03:31:18.180
MATT: It's a dex save on you, Grog, to try and
avoid it.

03:31:18.180 --> 03:31:21.419
TRAVIS: 15?

03:31:21.419 --> 03:31:23.441
MATT: What's your DC?

03:31:23.441 --> 03:31:24.667
SAM: 17.

03:31:24.667 --> 03:31:26.621
MATT: No. Full damage on this.

03:31:26.621 --> 03:31:28.296
LAURA: Oh shit!

03:31:28.296 --> 03:31:42.545
SAM: This could be it. Oh, this is it. Well,
maybe. 29.

03:31:42.545 --> 03:31:46.292
TRAVIS: Oh, 29 points of damage?

03:31:46.292 --> 03:31:50.516
MATT: Acid damage, yeah. Roll a constitution.

03:31:50.516 --> 03:31:53.857
TRAVIS: With the plus two to constitution from the
card.

03:31:53.857 --> 03:32:03.117
MATT: Well, plus one. The modifier gives you a
plus one. The DC is 15 this time.

03:32:03.117 --> 03:32:04.388
TRAVIS: 24.

03:32:04.388 --> 03:32:07.154
MATT: Okay. He stays up at one hit point.

03:32:07.154 --> 03:32:09.347
SAM: (screams) He's insane!

03:32:09.347 --> 03:32:11.668
MARISHA: He's undead!

03:32:11.668 --> 03:32:16.805
MATT: The DC's going to be 20, next time that
happens. You still have your movement.

03:32:16.805 --> 03:32:23.060
SAM: I'm going to go 50 feet anywhere. To the top
of that tower over there, I guess.

03:32:23.060 --> 03:32:24.241
MATT: Over here?

03:32:24.241 --> 03:32:30.254
SAM: Yeah. Can I get there? Or as far away from
him as I can get.

03:32:30.254 --> 03:32:35.422
MATT: You can get... all the way over here.

03:32:35.422 --> 03:32:38.076
SAM: I'm going to get lightninged, but that's
okay. I'll take it.

03:32:38.076 --> 03:32:41.346
MATT: It's better than a Grogning. All right, that
ends your turn.

03:32:41.346 --> 03:32:43.421
TRAVIS: You're on top of the fucking tower?

03:32:43.421 --> 03:32:52.080
MATT: Top of the round, the braziers all
(explosion noise) in the distance. No effect.

03:32:52.080 --> 03:32:53.546
Grog, your turn.

03:32:53.546 --> 03:33:01.111
TRAVIS: May I leap over the acid pit with the
Boots of Feral Leaping, knowing I might fall in.

03:33:01.111 --> 03:33:17.620
No, I'm in there. 23. Where are you going,
chicken? With my 50 feet of speed-- is there a

03:33:17.620 --> 03:33:19.328
chain hanging from the front of it?

03:33:19.328 --> 03:33:20.561
MATT: Yeah, right there.

03:33:20.561 --> 03:33:22.688
TRAVIS: Can I climb that with 50 feet of speed?
Probably not.

03:33:22.688 --> 03:33:25.197
MATT: You can climb it. We'll see how far you can
get.

03:33:25.197 --> 03:33:31.430
TRAVIS: No. I'm going to run into the tower and
start running up the stairs.

03:33:31.430 --> 03:33:39.375
MATT: You'll get partway into the first floor on
your 50. Are you going to dash

03:33:39.375 --> 03:33:41.127
to try and do the rest?

03:33:41.127 --> 03:33:43.001
TRAVIS: Yes, if it will get me to the top.

03:33:43.001 --> 03:33:44.645
MATT: It won't get you all the way to the top,
no.

03:33:44.645 --> 03:33:46.160
TRAVIS: Okay, that's fine. I'll dash.

03:33:46.160 --> 03:33:53.339
MATT: Okay, you'll get-- with your dash, into the
third floor, almost to the hatch. So you're up in

03:33:53.339 --> 03:33:55.778
the third floor right now. Tary?

03:33:55.778 --> 03:34:01.398
SAM: (giggles) I casually walk down the stairs.

03:34:01.398 --> 03:34:14.602
MATT: You come to the hatch, and Grog rushes up
into the third floor there. As you come down in

03:34:14.602 --> 03:34:16.083
the hatch.

03:34:16.083 --> 03:34:20.565
TRAVIS: I have a request. With your hands.
Please.

03:34:20.565 --> 03:34:21.780
SAM: With my hands?

03:34:21.780 --> 03:34:22.770
TRAVIS: Yes.

03:34:22.770 --> 03:34:23.905
LAURA: Don't.

03:34:23.905 --> 03:34:25.163
TRAVIS: I'm a simple man.

03:34:25.163 --> 03:34:34.212
SAM: All right. I can do that. (laughing) I can't
do that. You're so powerful. I'll probably miss!

03:34:34.212 --> 03:34:36.644
TRAVIS: You got it, man.

03:34:36.644 --> 03:34:41.483
SAM: If I miss, then I'm trapped in a room with
him!

03:34:41.483 --> 03:34:43.383
TRAVIS: I've got one hit point.

03:34:43.383 --> 03:34:45.208
SAM: But I could miss.

03:34:45.208 --> 03:34:47.196
LAURA: Kill him, Tary!

03:34:47.196 --> 03:34:51.079
TRAVIS: This is your chance to claim your bravery
for your house.

03:34:51.079 --> 03:34:52.385
SAM: Greatsword!

03:34:52.385 --> 03:34:55.228
MARISHA: You're getting him with a greatsword?

03:34:55.228 --> 03:34:58.187
SAM: That's what I've got. Greatsword.

03:34:58.187 --> 03:35:00.774
MATT: Your rod turns into a greatsword.

03:35:00.774 --> 03:35:03.428
TRAVIS: (laughing) The fucking thing.

03:35:03.428 --> 03:35:11.985
SAM: I'll do this crazy around and around thing
and try to do that with the greatsword. Oh, and

03:35:11.985 --> 03:35:14.230
can I set it on fire, first?

03:35:14.230 --> 03:35:15.167
MATT: Yes, you can.

03:35:15.167 --> 03:35:16.742
TRAVIS: Oh, good. Yeah.

03:35:16.742 --> 03:35:26.126
SAM: What am I rolling? What was that? 12 plus
eight plus two magic. That's 22.

03:35:26.126 --> 03:35:29.165
MATT: Hits. Roll damage.

03:35:29.165 --> 03:35:32.024
SAM: Three.

03:35:32.024 --> 03:35:35.469
MATT: Grog, make a constitution--

03:35:35.469 --> 03:35:38.284
SAM: Oh, it's 2d6. Four.

03:35:38.284 --> 03:35:41.237
(laughter)

03:35:41.237 --> 03:35:48.523
MATT: Roll a constitution saving throw. DC 20.

03:35:48.523 --> 03:35:50.688
TRAVIS: That's a natural 19.

03:35:50.688 --> 03:35:52.730
MARISHA: Oh my god, he's still fucking alive!

03:35:52.730 --> 03:35:54.189
SAM: What happened?!

03:35:54.189 --> 03:35:55.593
TRAVIS: Natural 19.

03:35:55.593 --> 03:35:57.182
SAM: (screams)

03:35:57.182 --> 03:35:59.730
TRAVIS: And I'd like to take my retaliation
strike.

03:35:59.730 --> 03:36:01.038
TALIESIN: Yeah!

03:36:01.038 --> 03:36:02.486
SAM: I still have movement.

03:36:02.486 --> 03:36:06.481
MATT: You do, after this. Retaliation is an
immediate reaction.

03:36:06.481 --> 03:36:20.233
SAM: I get a disengage. Didn't we go over this? I
did a melee weapon attack. Don't I get a disengage

03:36:20.233 --> 03:36:21.336
for free?

03:36:21.336 --> 03:36:25.480
MATT: As your feat, you mean?

03:36:25.480 --> 03:36:27.873
SAM: Yes! My Mobile feat.

03:36:27.873 --> 03:36:34.002
MATT: Right, but this isn't him getting a free
attack from you moving away. One of his barbarian

03:36:34.002 --> 03:36:37.729
abilities is if someone hits him with a melee
attack, he can immediately attack.

03:36:37.800 --> 03:36:39.168
SAM: Okay.

03:36:39.168 --> 03:36:41.631
MATT: He goaded you right into doing what he
wanted.

03:36:41.631 --> 03:36:43.212
TALIESIN: Oh my god.

03:36:43.212 --> 03:36:45.770
TRAVIS: How many hit points do you have?

03:36:45.770 --> 03:36:47.837
SAM: Enough.

03:36:47.837 --> 03:36:49.322
TRAVIS: Oh, okay.

03:36:49.322 --> 03:36:50.669
MATT: Make your attack, Grog.

03:36:50.669 --> 03:36:56.911
TRAVIS: Reckless. Come on, natural 20. No. 27.

03:36:56.911 --> 03:36:58.974
SAM: To hit? Sure.

03:36:58.974 --> 03:37:04.263
TRAVIS: 25 points of damage.

03:37:04.263 --> 03:37:05.810
SAM: That hurts.

03:37:05.810 --> 03:37:07.485
TRAVIS: But not enough.

03:37:07.485 --> 03:37:14.728
SAM: It hurts you, because I have a Shield of Fire
that burns anybody who attacks me with a melee

03:37:14.728 --> 03:37:19.720
attack. With 2d8 cold damage.

03:37:19.720 --> 03:37:27.659
TRAVIS: This fucking magic is too much for this
barbarian. I mean, goddamn. People are turning

03:37:27.659 --> 03:37:31.501
into flames, dragons, running around in a fucking
hamster ball,

03:37:31.501 --> 03:37:34.619
setting me on fucking cold damage...

03:37:34.619 --> 03:37:36.206
MATT: Roll some cold damage.

03:37:36.206 --> 03:37:38.287
SAM: Two. Nine.

03:37:38.287 --> 03:37:40.813
MATT: Make another constitution check with a DC
25, Grog.

03:37:40.813 --> 03:37:42.551
MARISHA: DC 25!

03:37:42.551 --> 03:37:51.071
LAURA: He has to roll a natural 20 in order to get
this. No. He has to roll a 19.

03:37:51.071 --> 03:37:53.581
SAM: He gets two rolls.

03:37:53.581 --> 03:37:58.573
TRAVIS: I have plus 12 as the modifier to the
roll. My constitution is plus 12.

03:37:58.573 --> 03:38:02.030
LAURA: Oh, a saving throw? Oh shit.

03:38:02.030 --> 03:38:05.147
TRAVIS: So I have to roll-- what's the math on
that?

03:38:05.147 --> 03:38:06.478
MATT: It's a 25.

03:38:06.478 --> 03:38:08.377
TRAVIS: 17 or higher?

03:38:08.377 --> 03:38:10.853
LAURA: It's not even that much. It's a 13 or
higher.

03:38:10.853 --> 03:38:15.505
MARISHA: He's going to make it.

03:38:15.505 --> 03:38:18.233
TRAVIS: Seven.

03:38:18.233 --> 03:38:20.981
MATT: Taryon, how do you want to do this?

03:38:20.981 --> 03:38:31.694
SAM: I want him to hit the blazing TD on my chest
and have the might of my name ricochet back with

03:38:31.694 --> 03:38:36.568
the power of energy. The Darrington name strikes
him down.

03:38:36.568 --> 03:38:45.430
MATT: The cold shatters you, and you feel the
ribcage break like brittle glass on the inside of

03:38:45.430 --> 03:38:50.784
your chest from the blast backward. You fall to
your knees, unable to move a muscle. You can feel

03:38:50.784 --> 03:38:55.858
the life barely beating through. Your body is
heaving with each heartbeat pulse. He's prostrate

03:38:55.858 --> 03:38:57.503
before you, Taryon, as you approach.

03:38:57.503 --> 03:39:05.804
SAM: I say, Doty, take this down. I win. And I
kick him over.

03:39:05.804 --> 03:39:12.978
MATT: As you hit the ground, as the last of the
cold damage has curled over your body and freezes

03:39:12.978 --> 03:39:20.105
you solid, you (shattering) shatter into thousands
of small, frozen pieces. The last T2 reference of

03:39:20.105 --> 03:39:31.697
the night, yep. As Taryon Darrington stands victor
of this round. As you stand there, breathing

03:39:31.697 --> 03:39:38.062
heavily, suddenly the stone top of the tower
cracks open, like it's being pulled apart by giant,

03:39:38.062 --> 03:39:45.632
invisible hands. And there you see, descending
from above, a gentleman in a large, dark cloak and

03:39:45.632 --> 03:39:54.484
a magnificent beard, and a glorious, well-kept
mane of hair. He lands. "Let this blessing of

03:39:54.484 --> 03:40:01.577
"Colville carry you into any dimension." He touches
your forehead and you feel the fates reach into

03:40:01.577 --> 03:40:09.738
you and plant you with a seed of possibility. And
then with that, a flash is gone. You awaken in

03:40:09.738 --> 03:40:16.852
your bed. Cold sweat. The next morning after you
went to sleep. You're not as powerful as you felt

03:40:16.852 --> 03:40:23.970
before. That was a crazy dream. But you look down
and you see this slight glow of white light across

03:40:23.970 --> 03:40:31.081
your sternum from underneath your silk pajamas,
and then it fades, and you feel like something

03:40:31.081 --> 03:40:36.945
from that dream is holding on. And that's where
we're going to end our game tonight.

03:40:36.945 --> 03:40:39.073
(cheering)

03:40:39.073 --> 03:40:40.519
TRAVIS: You got your fate dice.

03:40:40.519 --> 03:40:45.977
LAURA: Oh my god. And your parents are named after
Tony Stark's parents. How crazy is that?

03:40:45.977 --> 03:40:47.736
SAM: Oh, wait. They are?

03:40:47.736 --> 03:40:49.928
TRAVIS: How many hit points did you have left?

03:40:49.928 --> 03:40:51.283
SAM: I still had 30 or something.

03:40:51.283 --> 03:40:54.244
TALIESIN: He had 25.

03:40:54.244 --> 03:40:59.083
MATT: I'm curious. Where were you going to try and
Plane Shift Grog?

03:40:59.083 --> 03:41:02.690
MARISHA: Water Plane. Water dimension. You would
have just drowned.

03:41:02.690 --> 03:41:04.230
TALIESIN: Solid.

03:41:04.230 --> 03:41:09.743
MARISHA: I didn't know your charisma was-- I
thought you had zero.

03:41:09.743 --> 03:41:11.492
TRAVIS: It's plus one.

03:41:11.492 --> 03:41:17.532
MARISHA: All he had to roll was an 18 or lower.
Anything else.

03:41:17.532 --> 03:41:21.102
TRAVIS: That's why I was like, ugh, it's a 19.

03:41:21.102 --> 03:41:25.283
LAURA: Oh man. That was awesome.

03:41:25.283 --> 03:41:26.784
MATT: That was a great battle, guys.

03:41:26.784 --> 03:41:32.253
TRAVIS: That was a great map! That map was
amazing.

03:41:32.253 --> 03:41:35.285
MATT: I'm glad you guys had fun. I was hoping it
would be fun.

03:41:35.285 --> 03:41:38.467
TRAVIS: The three different varying--

03:41:38.467 --> 03:41:41.095
SAM: It was like a paintball field.

03:41:41.095 --> 03:41:45.895
MATT: That's what I wanted to make it feel like.
Little bunker areas.

03:41:45.895 --> 03:41:49.573
LAURA: You did have places that people that were
flying could hide.

03:41:49.573 --> 03:41:50.810
MATT: Yeah.

03:41:50.810 --> 03:41:55.373
TRAVIS: If we had tried to hit one of the spires
that created electricity,

03:41:55.373 --> 03:41:57.193
would that have ended that?

03:41:57.193 --> 03:42:02.395
MATT: Here? You could have destroyed it. Hitting
it would have done damage to it, but it would have

03:42:02.395 --> 03:42:04.585
prevented that from going off in that area.

03:42:04.585 --> 03:42:06.490
SAM: Were all the trunks the same thing?

03:42:06.490 --> 03:42:08.604
MATT: Yeah, each trunk had one healing potion. It
was whoever got there first.

03:42:08.604 --> 03:42:10.011
TALIESIN: And there was one trunk left?

03:42:10.011 --> 03:42:11.578
MATT: One trunk left that nobody went to.

03:42:11.578 --> 03:42:12.425
TRAVIS: Which one?

03:42:12.425 --> 03:42:14.631
MARISHA: The one that I was in for a lot of the
time.

03:42:14.631 --> 03:42:16.313
TALIESIN: I kept thinking about telling you.

03:42:16.313 --> 03:42:20.078
TRAVIS: Oh, really? The one down here in the lower
left?

03:42:20.078 --> 03:42:21.362
TALIESIN: Yeah, bottom left.

03:42:21.362 --> 03:42:23.430
MARISHA: It was the one I was camping out in.

03:42:23.430 --> 03:42:25.833
TALIESIN: But it wasn't my turn, so I didn't say
anything.

03:42:25.833 --> 03:42:30.203
MARISHA: I almost thought about taking it just so
no one else could have it, but never got to it.

03:42:30.203 --> 03:42:31.609
MATT: Well done, guys.

03:42:31.609 --> 03:42:34.532
TALIESIN: (giggles) That was nuts.

03:42:34.532 --> 03:42:41.783
MATT: Oh man. Well, when this campaign arc's over
and we have everybody available, hopefully, we'll

03:42:41.783 --> 03:42:47.325
probably have one final battle royale with
everyone max level, with Vax, with Pike, and see

03:42:47.325 --> 03:42:52.366
who comes through on that one. And whatever gift
boon I decide for that one, if it's similar or the

03:42:52.366 --> 03:42:55.263
same, will probably carry over to the next
campaign for their first new characters.

03:42:55.263 --> 03:42:56.632
Should be fun.

03:42:56.632 --> 03:43:00.465
MARISHA: Level 20 Keyleth is nasty. I get
unlimited Shapechange.

03:43:00.465 --> 03:43:08.177
TRAVIS: What do you mean, is nasty? You are nasty!
You were like the fucking Conclave. Jesus. The

03:43:08.177 --> 03:43:09.921
only thing you didn't turn into was a giant.

03:43:09.921 --> 03:43:11.764
MARISHA: I thought I was going to take the light
down.

03:43:11.764 --> 03:43:14.431
MATT: You had a 90% chance of just disappearing
and drowning.

03:43:14.431 --> 03:43:20.026
MARISHA: Yeah. I thought that's what he was going
to fucking do. I can't believe that.

03:43:20.026 --> 03:43:22.188
TRAVIS: That's true, yeah.

03:43:22.188 --> 03:43:24.963
MARISHA: You would have bamfed, and then it would
have been down to Tary and I.

03:43:24.963 --> 03:43:27.540
LAURA: I had no idea you could break out of my
fucking necklace!

03:43:27.540 --> 03:43:29.493
MATT: Nobody tried.

03:43:29.493 --> 03:43:34.019
TALIESIN: There's so many ways that you could have
died tonight.

